To group results by using MongoDB Search [faceted navigation](fts-facet-ref), you must index
any `string` field as the `token` type. To run the following
query and group the results by the `genres` field in the `movies`
collection, your index must resemble the following example:

```json
{
  "mappings": {
    "dynamic": true,
      "fields": {
        "genres": {
          "type": "token"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The sample query uses the following pipeline stages:

| Pipeline Stage | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| $search        | Searches for titles that contain summer in the title field by using the facet (MongoDB Search Operator) collector.Retrieves a count of the number of total movies in the results in each genre by using facets option.                                                                                           |
| $addFields     | Adds the paginationToken field to store the tokens for each document in the results generated by using the searchSequenceToken option.                                                                                                                                                                           |
| $limit         | Limits the results to 10 documents.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| $facet         | Returns the following fields:docs field, which contains only the title, released, and genres fields from the documents in the results and the paginationToken field.meta field, which contains a count of the total number of movies in the results in each genre that is stored in the $$SEARCH\_META variable. |

**Input:**

```json
db.movies.aggregate([
    {
      "$search": {
        "index": "pagination-tutorial",
        "facet": {
          "operator": {
            "text": {
              "path": "title",
              "query": "summer"
            } 
          },
          "facets": {
            "genresFacet": {
              "type": "string",
              "path": "genres"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    { 
      "$addFields": {
        "paginationToken" : { "$meta" : "searchSequenceToken" }
      }
    },
    { "$limit": 10 },
    {
      "$facet": {
        "docs": [
          { "$project":
            {
              "_id": 0,
              "title": 1,
              "released": 1,
              "genres": 1,
              "paginationToken" : 1
            }
          }
        ],
        "meta": [
          { "$replaceWith": "$$SEARCH_META" },
          { "$limit": 1 }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "$set": {
        "meta": {
          "$arrayElemAt": ["$meta", 0]
        }
      }
    }
])
```

